        1: active cancer (1)
        2: paralysis, paresis, recent immobilization of lower extremity (1)
        3: recently bedridden for >3 days, or major surgery in last 4 weeks (1)
        4: localized tenderness along distribution of the deep venous system (1)
        5: entire leg swollen (1)
        6: calf swelling by >3 cm compared to asymptomatic leg (1)
        7: pitting edema (greater in symptomatic leg) (1)
        8: collateral, non varicose superficial veins (1)
        9: alternative diagnosis as or more likely than dvt (-2)
}

Cheif_Sign_Notes:
* symmetric head circumference, length, and weight proportionally decreased. usually occurs early in pregnangy 1st or 2nd trimester. causes are intrinsic fetal factors or first-trimester insult like infecton

*asymmetric head circumference is spread realtive to decreased weight length. usually occurs later in pregnancy 3rd trimester. causes are often due to maternal factors. thought to result from adaptation to an unfavourable environment late in pregnancy
General_Notes:
*detalied pregnancy, and labour/delivery history,
*detalied physical exam,
*assess pattern growth (asymmetric vs  symmetric iugr)
